```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return strip(lowercase(replace(col, r"[-\s]" => '_')))
end
```

This function takes a string `col` as input and returns a lowercased, stripped version with spaces and hyphens replaced by underscores. The `strip` function is used to remove any leading or trailing whitespaces, the `lowercase` function is applied to make the entire name lowercase, and finally, `replace` is used to substitute spaces and hyphens with underscores using a regular expression.
